				<div style="clear: left;">
															<p>Hi Rick. I was wondering why you have not approached the school again. Did they identify your daughter with dyslexia first? Has the school tried to help her?<br />
If you meet with her teacher and discuss this with them and tell them how the situation is going it might get the ball rolling. I feel that school is the best place to start because that is where she spends most of her days. You have to advocate for her at school first and see what happens. Adding more work outside of school maybe overwhelming for her. Working with the school resources and reinforing it at home is a great help to her. Also the school maybe able to provide you with the name of someone outside of school that may help her. </p>
